    The gut microbiome and hypertension.
Several methodological and technological challenges remain in gut microbiome research, and the solutions involve minimizing confounding factors, establishing causality and acting globally to improve sample diversity. New clinical trials, precision microbiome medicine and computational methods such as Mendelian randomization have the potential to enable leveraging of the microbiome for translational applications to lower blood pressure.
